    "XpertAI identifies the presence of a heteroatom bonded to three oxygen atoms, tertiary amine and carbon-oxygen single bond to be associated with the toxicity of molecules.",
    "The generated XpertAI explanation summarizes: \"The analysis of features identified by XAI in relation to the toxicity of small molecules reveals several key insights.",
    "The presence of a heteroatom bonded to three oxygen atoms, such as in phosphate groups, is associated with increased chemical reactivity due to the electronegative nature of oxygen atoms, potentially influencing toxicity.",
    "Tertiary amines, known for their nucleophilic properties, may interact with electrophilic sites in biological systems, contributing to toxicity.",
    "Additionally, carbon-oxygen single bonds, prevalent in functional groups like alcohols and ethers, can affect the solubility and reactivity of molecules, thereby impacting their toxicity."
